However, it is difficult to obtain the removal of doubtful records in the trademark register, and this is costly.
The process may last up to nine years, with a vague outcome.
Pattloch describes cases in which the court rejected claims, since after a long time the contested name became a “market reality”.
If the claimant is not lucky, he will even have to pay the plagiarator because he damaged his trademark in China, says Pattloch.
